# Mobile App (Expo) — Setup & Implementation

**ALWAYS follow these when working in `mobile/`.**

## Reference Docs

- **Build guide:** `docs/MOBILE_APP_BUILD_GUIDE.md` — dependencies, env, path aliases, CORS, errors
- **Plan:** `.cursor/plans/mobile_app_implementation_strategy.plan.md` — phases, order, files
- **Design refs:** `docs/mobile-design-references.md` — Revolut, Fuse patterns

## Dependencies

- Use `npx expo install <pkg>` for Expo packages (expo-secure-store, expo-router, expo-blur, etc.)
- Use `npm install` for non-Expo (axios, @tanstack/react-query, @gorhom/bottom-sheet)
- **DO NOT** add packages that require native code not in Expo Go unless using dev build

## Imports & Path Aliases

- Use `@/` alias: `import { api } from '@/services/api'`
- Requires `babel-plugin-module-resolver` + `tsconfig.json` paths (see build guide)
- Import order: 1) React/Expo, 2) services/hooks, 3) components, 4) constants

## API & Auth

- API URL: `process.env.EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL` or `Constants.expoConfig?.extra?.apiUrl`
- Token storage: `expo-secure-store` (not AsyncStorage for production)
- Same backend endpoints as web; reuse API structure from `Frontend/src/services/`

## Structure

- `app/` — Expo Router file-based routes; `(tabs)/` for tab navigator
- `services/` — api.ts, auth.ts
- `context/` — AuthContext, ThemeContext
- `components/` — reusable UI

## UI (React Native)

- Use React Native primitives: `View`, `Text`, `Pressable`, `ScrollView`, `FlatList`/`FlashList`
- **DO NOT** use shadcn/ui or web components — they are for Frontend only
- Use `@expo/vector-icons` or `lucide-react-native` for icons

## Mobile App — Out of Scope (Web Only)

**DO NOT implement these screens in the mobile app.** They are web-only; use the web app for these features.

- Leads
- Vendors
- Employees
- Payroll
- Users / Team management
- Prescriptions (pharmacy)
- Drugs (pharmacy)
- Foot Traffic
- Accounting

## Rules from .cursorrules (Adapted)

- **No shadows** — use borders, flat design
- **Primary color** #166534
- **Button order** — secondary before primary
- **Business type** — check `activeTenant?.businessType` for center tab action (Camera vs Plus)
- **Constants** — define in `constants/` instead of magic strings
